citation.excerpt: PyTorch implementation of Glow, Generative Flow with Invertible 1x1 Convolutions (https://arxiv.org/abs/1807.03039)

description.excerpt: I have trained model on vanilla celebA dataset. Seems like works well. I found that learning rate (I have used 1e-4 without scheduling), learnt prior, number of bits (in this cases, 5), and using sigmoid function at the affine coupling layer instead of exponential function is beneficial to training a model.
